verbose_text: Similarly, the A 1 R antagonist DPCPX (1-50 muM), which blocks the actions of endogenously released adenosine to elicit an increase in burst frequency when DA is present, failed to modulate either the frequency (XREF_FIG; P> 0.05, n = 7) or the amplitude (XREF_FIG; P> 0.05, n = 7) of bursting in the absence of DA or SKF 38393.
